    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nI  noticed that currently `clangd.lua` in the repo is launching clangd like this:\n\n```\n cmd = { 'clangd' },\n```\n\nWould it be better to do it like this?\n\n```\n  cmd = { 'clangd', '--background-index' },\n```\n\nThat's really the only difference currently between my local config and the repo. This should help with the subsequent loads, since clangd then persists index after initial run.\n\n",
